# WOR-310 Phase B intentionally drops the ``USER worthless`` directive
# so deploy/start.py can run as root briefly, resolve the two service
# uids (worthless-proxy=10001, worthless-crypto=10002), chown the
# share files, and call setresuid before exec'ing uvicorn.  Dockle's
# CIS-DI-0001 check ("last user should not be root") sees the
# image-default and fires WARN — but the runtime never actually runs
# as root past the priv-drop dance.  The runtime security claim is
# verified by the two-uid integration tests in
# tests/test_install_docker.py and the priv-drop unit suite in
# tests/cli/test_sidecar_lifecycle_priv_drop.py.
CIS-DI-0001
